# SSH Configuration
# Managed by chezmoi

# --- Identity routing: human vs. AI agent ----------------------------------
# The YubiKey (id_ed25519_sk) is for the human at the keyboard alone. AI agents
# (Claude Code, Codex, …) stamp their own environment markers onto every process
# they spawn; an interactive human shell never carries them. The ~/.ssh/agent-context
# probe reads those markers and routes auth accordingly:
#
#   • Agent session  → software deploy key (id_ed25519), no agent, no forwarding.
#                      The hardware key is unreachable, so no PIN/touch is ever
#                      demanded — agents can no longer hijack the terminal.
#   • Human session  → the YubiKey, exactly as before.
#
# These two Match blocks precede every Host block on purpose: for IdentityFile,
# IdentityAgent and ForwardAgent the first value obtained wins, so the gate
# decides the identity before any host default can. IdentitiesOnly + IdentityAgent
# none in the agent branch guarantee that branch can reach *only* the software key
# — even for hosts not named below. Fails closed: if id_ed25519 is absent, the
# agent is simply denied (publickey), never fallen back to the hardware key.
Match exec "~/.ssh/agent-context"
    IdentitiesOnly yes
    IdentityAgent none
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
    ForwardAgent no

Match exec "! ~/.ssh/agent-context"
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519_sk
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

